\f1\b Definition:
\f0\b0  The PMF of a discrete random variable gives the probability of each outcome .\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +2
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\b Visualization:
\f0\b0  The distribution can be visualized as a bar diagram where the x-axis represents the possible values of the RV and the height of the bar at value $a$ is the probability $Pr[X=a]$ .\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +1
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 
\f1\b Legitimacy Condition:
\f0\b0  For a discrete random variable, the sum of all probabilities in the PMF must equal 1: $\\sum_\{i\} P\\\{X=i\\\} = 1$ .\uc0\u8232 
\fs22 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 +3
\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
